---
import Layout from "@/layouts/main.astro"
import { buttonVariants } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Card, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card"
import { Table, TableBody, TableHead, TableHeader, TableRow, TableCell } from "@/components/ui/table"
import { BASE } from "@/lib/url"
import { LightningIcon } from "@phosphor-icons/react"
import { TIER_THRESHOLDS } from "@/lib/scoring"
---

<Layout
  title="Where Builders Meet | How It Works — Scoring, Submissions & Community"
  description="How guild base scoring works in Where Winds Meet, how to submit your build, and how the community votes. Everything you need to know to get started."
>
  <div class="max-w-6xl space-y-10">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
      <h1 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2"><LightningIcon weight="duotone" className="size-6 text-primary" /> How it works</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm">The community hub for Where Winds Meet builders. <span class="whitespace-nowrap">Join us on <a href="https://discord.gg/Qygt9u26Bn" class="text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary transition-colors" data-umami-event="discord_cta_click">Discord ↗</a></span></p>
    </div>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">The origin</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Guild bases in <strong class="text-foreground"><a href="https://www.wherewindsmeetgame.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Where Winds Meet</a></strong> were too good to keep secret, so this place was born.
        A bot watches the Discord forum, picks up submissions, counts reactions, and syncs the showcase automatically <strong class="text-foreground">several times a day</strong>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">Community votes</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 leading-relaxed">
        Only reactions on the <strong>first post</strong> of a thread are counted. Reactions on replies are ignored.
      </p>

      <div class="rounded-xl ring-1 ring-border overflow-hidden">
        <Table>
          <TableHeader className="bg-muted/40 text-muted-foreground">
            <TableRow>
              <TableHead className="text-muted-foreground">Reaction</TableHead>
              <TableHead className="text-muted-foreground">Points</TableHead>
              <TableHead className="text-muted-foreground">Notes</TableHead>
            </TableRow>
          </TableHeader>
          <TableBody>
            <TableRow>
              <TableCell className="text-lg">⭐</TableCell>
              <TableCell className="font-mono font-semibold">+2</TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground">Reserve for the builds you consider truly the best. Use it sparingly.</TableCell>
            </TableRow>
            <TableRow>
              <TableCell className="text-lg">👍 🔥 ❤️</TableCell>
              <TableCell className="font-mono font-semibold">+1</TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground">Any positive reaction. Use whichever fits your impression.</TableCell>
            </TableRow>
          </TableBody>
        </Table>
      </div>

      <details class="group rounded-xl ring-1 ring-border overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-2 cursor-pointer px-4 py-3 bg-muted/40 text-sm font-medium select-none hover:bg-muted/60 transition-colors list-none">
          <span>Build your own voting scale</span>
          <span class="text-muted-foreground text-xs group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-4 py-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            You can react with <strong class="text-foreground">multiple emojis</strong> on the same post. Each combination adds up, so your reactions become a personal score you give that guild.
            Using a consistent scale makes the rankings more meaningful for everyone.
          </p>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">Here is one way to think about it:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5 font-mono text-xs">
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="text-base">⭐👍🔥❤️</span><span class="text-muted-foreground">= +5 pts — absolute best, a must-see</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="text-base">⭐👍🔥</span><span class="text-muted-foreground">= +4 pts — outstanding, one of your favourites</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="text-base">👍🔥❤️</span><span class="text-muted-foreground">= +3 pts — excellent, clearly above average</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="text-base">👍🔥</span><span class="text-muted-foreground">= +2 pts — really good, worth a star</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="text-base">👍</span><span class="text-muted-foreground">= +1 pt — nice build, positive impression</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="text-base text-muted-foreground">—</span><span class="text-muted-foreground">= +0 pts — no strong feeling either way</span></li>
          </ul>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            You are free to pick any scale that feels right to you. What matters is staying consistent: if you give ⭐ to 50 guilds, it loses its meaning. Use it sparingly so it signals something real.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">Voter weight</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Votes are not all equal. The more guilds you have voted on, the more weight each of your reactions carries. Voting on a single guild barely registers.
      </p>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800 bg-emerald-50/60 dark:bg-emerald-950/30 px-4 py-4 space-y-3">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300">How to make your vote count</p>
        <ol class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground list-decimal list-inside">
          <li>Browse the <a href={`${BASE}/`} class="text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary transition-colors">showcase</a> and visit guilds you haven't seen yet.</li>
          <li>React honestly on each thread (⭐, 👍, 🔥, ❤️) — only the first post counts.</li>
          <li>Keep exploring: the more guilds you've voted on, the more your votes matter.</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">You can check your own voting spread at any time with <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">/my-votes</code> on the Discord server.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-orange-200 dark:border-orange-800 bg-orange-50/60 dark:bg-orange-950/30 px-4 py-3 space-y-1.5">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-orange-700 dark:text-orange-300">Balanced voting matters</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          Fair voting is what keeps this project alive. Without it, rankings lose their value and the community that depends on them suffers.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          Spreading your votes across many guilds is not enough on its own. Giving full points to one guild while leaving minimal reactions on everything else is not considered balanced voting.
          Try to rate each guild honestly based on what you actually think of it.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed italic">
          Example: giving ⭐👍🔥❤️ to a single guild while leaving only 👍 across ten others raises fairness concerns.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          Voters identified as abusing the system can be excluded from scoring entirely.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 bg-amber-50/60 dark:bg-amber-950/30 px-4 py-3 space-y-1">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">Scoring is still maturing</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          The community is young. Many excellent guilds have low scores simply because not enough people have visited them yet.
          Scoring is evolving, you can see your score lowering sometimes due to different reasons such as normalization.  
          Scoring will become fairer as more voters engage broadly (expect constant changes).
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">Tiers</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Builds are grouped into tiers based on votes, for recognition (more than competition). <a href={`${BASE}/contribute`} class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Post yourself your own base</a> to give it the best chance.
        Voting takes time so please be patient. We try our best to highlight different guilds every week.  
      </p>

      <div class="rounded-xl ring-1 ring-border overflow-hidden">
        <Table>
          <TableHeader className="bg-muted/40 text-muted-foreground">
            <TableRow>
              <TableHead className="text-muted-foreground">Tier</TableHead>
              <TableHead className="text-muted-foreground">Threshold</TableHead>
              <TableHead className="text-muted-foreground">What it means</TableHead>
            </TableRow>
          </TableHeader>
          <TableBody>
<TableRow>
              <TableCell>
                <span class="tier-master inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-bold text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-200" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(251,191,36,0.18) 0%, rgba(245,158,11,0.12) 100%);">
                  <span class="size-1.5 rounded-full bg-amber-300 shrink-0"></span>Master
                </span>
              </TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Top {TIER_THRESHOLDS.master * 100}%</TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Exceptional community recognition</TableCell>
            </TableRow>
            <TableRow>
              <TableCell>
                <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-sky-600 dark:text-sky-200 ring-1 ring-inset ring-sky-400/40" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(56,189,248,0.14) 0%, rgba(99,102,241,0.12) 100%);">
                  <span class="size-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-300 shrink-0"></span>Diamond
                </span>
              </TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Top {TIER_THRESHOLDS.diamond * 100}%</TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Strongly appreciated by the community</TableCell>
            </TableRow>
            <TableRow>
              <TableCell>
                <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-cyan-700 dark:text-cyan-100 ring-1 ring-inset ring-cyan-200/50" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(207,250,254,0.18) 0%, rgba(186,230,253,0.12) 100%);">
                  <span class="size-1.5 rounded-full bg-cyan-200 shrink-0"></span>Platinum
                </span>
              </TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Top {TIER_THRESHOLDS.platinum * 100}%</TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Well received by the community</TableCell>
            </TableRow>
            <TableRow>
              <TableCell>
                <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 text-xs text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300 ring-1 ring-inset ring-amber-400/35" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(251,191,36,0.14) 0%, rgba(245,158,11,0.08) 100%);">
                  <span class="size-1.5 rounded-full bg-amber-400 shrink-0"></span>Gold
                </span>
              </TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Good score</TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Guilds that could hide hidden gems</TableCell>
            </TableRow>
            <TableRow>
              <TableCell>
                <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 text-xs text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 ring-1 ring-inset ring-zinc-400/30" style="background: rgba(113,113,122,0.08);">
                  <span class="size-1.5 rounded-full bg-zinc-400 shrink-0"></span>Silver
                </span>
              </TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Low score</TableCell>
              <TableCell className="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Listed but not yet referenced by the builder</TableCell>
            </TableRow>
          </TableBody>
        </Table>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-sky-200 dark:border-sky-800 bg-sky-50/60 dark:bg-sky-950/30 px-4 py-3 space-y-1">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300">Why does my guild have a low score or grow slowly?</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          Scouted guilds start near zero. To grow faster, post your own thread in <strong class="text-foreground">#guild-base-showcase</strong> with screenshots: more visibility brings more reactions, which raises your tier. Keep in mind that voters are volunteers, so progress may take time.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-base font-medium">Discord roles</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-base mt-0.5">🏗️</span>
          <span><a href={`${BASE}/contribute?role=builder`} class="font-bold underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Builder</a>: awarded to users who post their own guild or solo base in the showcase channels</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-base mt-0.5">🗺️</span>
          <span><a href={`${BASE}/contribute?role=scout`} class="font-bold underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Guild Cartographer</a>: granted to members who consistently scout and document guild bases across the community</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-base mt-0.5">🗳️</span>
          <span><a href={`${BASE}/contribute?role=voter`} class="font-bold underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Critic</a>: awarded to active community voters who engage across many guilds</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-base mt-0.5">👁️</span>
          <span><a href={`${BASE}/contribute?role=voter`} class="font-bold underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Trusted Eye</a>: granted by moderators to members recognized for their expertise and quality feedback. Trusted Eyes carry more voting weight</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <Card>
      <CardContent className="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-4">
        <div class="flex-1">
          <p class="font-medium text-sm">Want to get involved?</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-0.5">Join the community Discord or check how to contribute.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-2 shrink-0">
          <a href="https://discord.gg/Qygt9u26Bn" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class={buttonVariants({ size: "lg" })} data-umami-event="discord_cta_click">Discord ↗</a>
          <a href={`${BASE}/contribute`} class={buttonVariants({ variant: "outline", size: "lg" })}>Contribute</a>
        </div>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  </div>
</Layout>
